South African Stocks: Anglo, AngloGold, Optimum, Harmony Move

-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 
2011-07-26T16:12:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/south-african-stocks-anglo-american-anglogold-harmony-move.html
The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index
declined 197.11, or 0.6 percent, to 31,863.73 by the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg, after rising 0.2 percent yesterday.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.  Anglo American Plc (AGL)  , the diversified mining company
that makes up 10 percent of the benchmark  stock index , closed at
its highest in more than two weeks, gaining 1.70 rand, or 0.5
percent, to 336.06 rand.  De Beers , the world’s biggest diamond
producer, in which Anglo American has a 45 percent stake,
reported a 33 percent increase in first-half rough-diamonds
sales by Diamond Trading Co., the producer’s trading arm, to
$3.49 billion.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  , Africa’s largest gold
producer, slumped to its lowest in two weeks, declining 9.48
rand, or 3.1 percent, to 293.27 rand. A strike at gold mines
owned by AngloGold,  Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI)   and Harmony Gold
Mining Co. (HAR SJ) in  South Africa  will begin on July 28, the
National Union of Mineworkers said in an e-mailed statement
today.  Gold Fields, the continent’s second-biggest producer,
dropped 2.78 rand, or 2.6 percent, to 104.20 rand.  Harmony, Africa’s third-largest gold producer, declined
2.70 rand, or 2.8 percent, to 94.30 rand.  Optimum Coal Holdings (OPT)  Ltd sank to its lowest
since October 2010, dropping 50 cents, or 2 percent, to 24.50
rand. The group said 73 percent of its workers have joined a
strike by South African coal miners. The company is operating at
10 percent to 20 percent of its capacity because of the strike,
Commercial Manager Kobus Breytenbach said by telephone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
